def: A particular proposition, as opposed to a universal one. SeeSubaltern, 2.
At a distance, but within view; yonder. [Poetic]Read thy lot in yon celestial sign. Milton.Though fast yon shower be fleeting. Keble.
To cover, as part of a rope, with marline, marking a pecularhitch at each turn to prevent unwinding. Marling spike. (Naut.) Seeunder Marline.
A direction in written or printed music to return to the properpitch after having played an octave higher.
An indefinite feeling of uneasiness, or of being sick or ill atease.
Of or pertaining to the rictus; as, rictal bristles.
